title: Parking Space - means an enclosed or unenclosed, covered or open area or area provided by mechanical means sufficient in size to park vehicle
clause_text: Parking Space - means an enclosed or unenclosed, covered or open area or area provided by mechanical means sufficient in size to park vehicle. Parking spaces shall be served by a driveway connecting them with a street or alley and permitting ingress or egress of vehicles. Partition - means an interior non-load-bearing barrier, one storey or part-storey in height.
